{"slug": "rune", "root": "rune", "category": "item", "gloss": "a letter of magical power", "definition": "A rune is a letter of magical power — one of the angular characters of the Germanic writing systems, named for the secret it was thought to hold.", "history": "Old English *rūn* means 'secret, mystery, whisper'; the runic letters were named for the hidden power that knowing them conferred, and the Norse Eddas have Odin win them in self-sacrifice. The Finnish borrowing *runo* means 'poem, song.' Magic uses 'Rune' for a cycle of Aura enchantments — magical letters fixed onto a permanent.", "def_sources": [{"label": "Etymonline, s.v. rune", "where": "Etymology reference"}, {"label": "Bosworth–Toller, s.v. rūn", "where": "Classical lexica"}], "commentary": "The gap here is between a thin medieval record and a lavish modern system. Kieckhefer notes the sources give us Woden's mastery of the runic alphabet and healing charms, and the *Libri runarum* fused Scandinavian runes with hermetic talismanic magic — but nothing like the comprehensive 'runic magic' of later occultism. That system is largely a nineteenth- and twentieth-century construction: the Germanic esotericism of Guido von List, the SS appropriation of runic sigils, and neo-pagan reconstruction. Ronald Hutton and others caution against reading these elaborate schemes back onto the medieval evidence; the modern *-ism* is the invention, not the letters.", "commentary_sources": [{"label": "Richard Kieckhefer, Magic in the Middle Ages", "where": "Medieval magic (PDF)"}, {"label": "Page & Rider, The Routledge History of Medieval Magic", "where": "Medieval magic (PDF)"}, {"label": "Ronald Hutton, on modern paganism and the runic revival", "where": "Reference"}], "is_keyword": false, "etymology": {"origin": "Old English rūn ‘secret, mystery, whisper’ ← Proto-Germanic *rūnō", "first": "before 900", "note": "The runic letters were named for secrecy itself — to know the runes was to know hidden things. The Finnish loan ‘runo’ means ‘poem, song.’", "hook": "An alphabet whose name means ‘secret.’", "lang": "Old English"}, "essay": null, "sources": ["Etymonline (Douglas Harper)", "Wiktionary", "classical lexica (Lewis & Short, LSJ, Bosworth–Toller)", "Ted's historical-magic DBs (WitchcraftStudiesDB, AgrippaDOP, MedievalMagicDB)"], "stats": {"flavor_total": 19, "oracle_total": 8, "in_flavor_cards": 18, "in_oracle_cards": 6, "name_match_count": 32, "by_variant": {"rune": 13, "runes": 11, "runic": 3}, "first_year": 1997, "colors": {"W": 19, "U": 13, "B": 5, "R": 11, "C": 6, "G": 7}, "by_year": {"1997": 2, "1998": 7, "2003": 1, "2005": 1, "2007": 1, "2008": 2, "2013": 1, "2014": 1, "2016": 2, "2017": 1, "2018": 1, "2019": 3, "2020": 4, "2021": 14, "2022": 2, "2023": 2, "2024": 4, "2025": 2, "2026": 1}}, "cards": [{"id": "1a128c02-febf-4ce6-b4d1-28274b5c4ff0", "name": "Ancient Runes", "set": "TMP", "set_name": "Tempest", "released": "1997-10-14", "type_line": "Enchantment", "rarity": "uncommon", "colors": ["R"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/e/3/e315c1c2-436e-48ff-9214-938697178393.jpg?1782720944", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/e/3/e315c1c2-436e-48ff-9214-938697178393.jpg?1782720944", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/tmp/161/ancient-runes?utm_source=api", "local": "img/rune/1a128c02-febf-4ce6-b4d1-28274b5c4ff0.jpg"}, {"id": "469c4b77-733e-472b-aeae-6015b409beb2", "name": "Rune of Protection: Artifacts", "set": "USG", "set_name": "Urza's Saga", "released": "1998-10-12", "type_line": "Enchantment", "rarity": "uncommon", "colors": ["W"], "img_small": "https://cards.scryfall.io/small/front/e/1/e18cce33-92be-4189-9f99-cb47bd617fd2.jpg?1782720746", "img_normal": "https://cards.scryfall.io/normal/front/e/1/e18cce33-92be-4189-9f99-cb47bd617fd2.jpg?1782720746", "scryfall_uri": "https://scryfall.com/card/usg/35/rune-of-protection:-artifacts?utm_source=api", "local": "img/rune/469c4b77-733e-472b-aeae-6015b409beb2.jpg"}, {"id": "b027302f-80c2-